                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "Lyophilized faecal samples were used to achieve better metabolite coverage. Metabolites were extracted with 1 ml of ice-cold methanol: water (8:2) from 80 mg of lyophilized samples in a bath ultrasonicator (Bioruptor TM UCD-200, Diagenode, USA) at 4 \u00b0C for 30 min followed by 2 min of vortexing. The supernatant was extracted by centrifugation at 18,000 x g for 15 min at 4 \u00b0C and dried at 50 \u00b0C under a gentle stream of nitrogen gas. To remove the residual water molecules from the samples, 100 \u00b5l of toluene was added to the dry residue and evaporated completely at 50 \u00b0C under nitrogen gas. Dry extracted metabolites were first derivatized with 50 \u00b5l of methoxyamine hydrochloride (MOX) in pyridine (20 mg/ml) at 60 \u00b0C for 2 hr, and the second derivatization was performed with 100 \u00b5l of MSTFA in 1% TMCS at 60 \u00b0C for 45 min to form trimethylsilyl (TMS) derivatives. Finally, 150 \u00b5l of the TMS derivatives was transferred into a GC glass vial inserts and subjected to GC-MS analysis.",
